g Guy and demanded Shrew in exchange for an antidote. The US government\'s toxicologist provided his own antidote, and X-Factor and the Shrew confronted Cyber and the Belles. X-Factor joined by [[Jamie Madrox|Multiple Man]] and [[Quicksilver (comics)|Quicksilver]] overpowered their attackers, and Shrew herself gathered the courage to knock Cyber into the path of an oncoming subway train.{{Issue|date=September 2011}}\\n\\nIt is unknown if Shrew lost or kept her mutant powers after the [[Decimation (comics)|M-Day]].\\n\\n==Powers and abilities==\\nMarilyn can transform into a large anthropomorphic [[soricidae]]. This form gives her enhanced strength, speed, agility, and senses, as well as razor sharp claws and fangs.\\n\\n==References==\\n{{reflist}}\\n\\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shrew (Comics)}}\\n[[Category:Female supervillains]]\\n[[Category:Fictional shapeshifters]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics mutants]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics supervillains]]\\n\\n{{Marvel-villain-stub}}"}]}}}}'